======================================================================================================================
BUGS — URGENT FIXES
======================================================================================================================

[BUG] flaskr/quotes/fetchers/stooq.py:33 — unguarded index into symbols list causes IndexError
    `data = data['symbols'][0]` crashes when Stooq returns an empty symbols array (e.g. bad ticker).
    The comment acknowledges this but there is no fix. Wraps the whole quote refresh in an unhandled exception.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

[BUG] flaskr/apps/wallet/templates/wallet/wallet.html:29 — JSON.parse() wrapping a JS object literal
    `const categoryAllocation = JSON.parse({{ allocation | tojson }});`
    `tojson` emits a JS object/array literal inline; passing it to JSON.parse() coerces it to the string
    "[object Object]" and throws SyntaxError. Should be: `const categoryAllocation = {{ allocation | tojson }};`
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

[BUG] flaskr/apps/wallet/static/wallet/wallet_sparklines.js:11 — slice(-1) when date is not found
    `historicalData.t.findIndex(...)` returns -1 when the start date is before all stored timestamps.
    `asset.value.slice(-1)` then takes only the last data point instead of all of them, giving a
    one-point sparkline and a completely wrong % return value.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

[BUG] flaskr/apps/assets/trash.py:14, flaskr/apps/quotes/index.py:75,
      flaskr/apps/pricing/listAll.py:52, flaskr/apps/assets/list.py:105
    Deprecated PyMongo methods: .update() and .insert() were removed in PyMongo 4.
    Replace with .update_one() / .insert_one() consistently across the codebase.
